data.title: Bill Macy: References
data.meta_description: B - Free download as Word Doc (.doc / .docx), PDF File (.pdf), Text File (.txt) or read online for free. Bill Macy is an American actor born in 1922 in Revere, Massachusetts. He is known for his role as Walter Findlay on the sitcom Maude and for appearances in films like The Jerk. This article needs additional citations to verify details about Macy's life and career. It flags the need for expansion on Macy as both a film and television actor born in the 1920s.
